The paper deals with generating pseudorandom numbers, which is a topic closely related to cryptography and security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves matrix operations, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of pre-generated matrices suggests a possible application in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the comparison of the quality of random numbers generated with other algorithms involves statistical analysis, which is a topic in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
